@node Future, ,Tips, Mixed
@section The Future of Cthugha for Linux

Some plans I have with Cthugha for Linux:

@itemize @bullet

@item Make it more independent from Linux. I think @code{xcthugha}
should run on every unix system fast enough at least when using just
random data or a sound file as input.

@item Cut it down a little bit. This has already started. Screen saver
and DGA support are no longer included. More things might
follow. The whole thing is just getting too big for me. I will 
remove parts for which good alternatives exist or which are useless.

@item User interface. The current user interface is not really good --
here are some changes necessary.

@item Copying Policy. This is definitely not change. I will never charge
you for private use. I think about putting the whole thing under the GNU
public license.

@end itemize





